				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">All roms have a prg size of 2^n (32k, 64k, 128k, etc) so many emus use "0xFFFF &amp; (prg_banks - 1)" to refer to the last bank. I know I do, at least.
<br />In your case, it would mean that the third bank is ignored and the second bank is used as if it were the last one.</div>

