					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, just watch the pinout of an EPROM. You have X pins of adress imput, adding one pin will double the size of the ROM, removing one pin will half it. You'll definitly need to have a 64kb PRG rom. The only way to have odd ROM size would be to combine two different ROM chip with two different sizes, I know that many SNES games does that.</div>

					
