					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Hum, I'm not sure that you got it.
<br />Unless you're re-inventing a new mapper like I said above, you can't have ROM size that isn't 2^n, so this is **NOT** possible with MMC3. Just look at all games and demos out there, they all have a 2^n PRG chip and 2^n CHR chip. May some old stupid demoes of the same style as "junkdemo" does, but if any does this is just gabrage.
<br />This is just a glich in the iNES header, they could decide to input "number of times you have to double the size of a 16kb PRG-ROM" instead of "number of 16kb PRG-ROM bank". Also, there is not always 16kb banks, but also 8kb or 32 kb from the various mappers. The smallest ROM possible is still 16kb.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
